{"title": "Melting of Molly", "description": "Meet Molly: a quirky, spirited twenty-five-year old, widowed for 6 years, living in picturesque Hillsboro with her aunt amidst gossipy neighbors, on a strict diet, and in serious boy trouble. There's Arthur, her childhood sweetheart; then, there's the enigmatic, charming Judge Wade; and of course, there's her cousin Tom; and then, her infuriating neighbor, John Moore... But who will melt her heart?<br><br>It is Arthur's return, and his seemingly simple request of wanting to see her in the same blue dress she wore when he left, that throws everything into turmoil...<br><br>Sometimes, one can only find some solace in one's garden.<br><br>Narrated in a refreshingly modern and playful style by none other than Molly herself, this book is the British magazine version; there\u2019s a significantly different American novel version.(Summary by Elli, Julie VW and Stav Nisser)", "duration": 8973, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "5266", "name": " Maria Thompson Daviess"}], "coverArt": "https://www.archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt5/Melting_Molly_1005.jpg", "copyright_year": "1912", "genres": ["General Fiction", "Romance"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Neeru Iyer"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Sarah Jennings"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Stav Nisser"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "Leaf I. The Bachelor's-Buttons.", "readers": [3885], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/melting_of_molly_0908_librivox/meltingofmolly_1_daviess_64kb.mp3", "duration": 941}, {"section": 2, "title": "Leaf II. A Love-Letter, Loaded.", "readers": [3885], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/melting_of_molly_0908_librivox/meltingofmolly_2_daviess_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1003}, {"section": 3, "title": "Leaf III.", "readers": [4111], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/melting_of_molly_0908_librivox/meltingofmolly_3_daviess_64kb